title: 'Document: It''s nice that copying doesn''t change buffer state.'
pid: dc2db4c0-122d-4684-bb3b-65e68112e2b9
body: |2-
  That lets you copy a node somewhere else, edit it there,
  (importantly) save, and the collateral changes will be reflected.
  (Collateral buffers with unsaved changes might,
  I can't remember, not be writeable to.
  If they're not it might be good.)
